---
import { IHeroProps } from "@types";

const { name, about } = Astro.props as IHeroProps;
---

<section>
  <p class="dark:text-light mt-[117px]">Hey, I’m</p>
  <h1 class="mb-8">{name}</h1>
  <ul class="mb-8 list-disc ml-5">
    <li class="dark:text-light text-lg">
      A dude who ❤️ the frontend aspect of web development.
    </li>
    <li class="dark:text-light text-lg">
      A pilot who crash-landed on a webpage (literally).
    </li>
    <li class="dark:text-light text-lg">
      A beardo who drinks coffee for the day and pumps code for the night.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h2 class="mb-8"></h2>
  <p class="dark:text-light text-lg">
    I always aspired to be a fighter pilot and was an avid fan of the Ace Combat
    game series. Then I saw a dude edit out his grades by editing the HTML of
    the webpage, and I fell in love.
  </p>
  <br />
  <p class="dark:text-light text-lg">
    I love learning new things and keeping myself up-to-date in the boiling mess
    of a world called Web Development. Right now, I'm learning GSAP in order to
    make those cool animations, other than getting my head around Angular and
    React Query, of course.
  </p>
</section>
